Diagram 2 (Pae)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's cut at 1 is a sharp move based on the proverb stating, "the enemy's key point is your own."
\par
\par Black 2 is an unavoidable response and then if white plays dansu at 3, up to 5, a pae is created. Is this the best result?
\par
\par In fact, there is a way for white to capture black. Please think about it a little bit more.
\par }
